{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/blepharitis/diagnosis/clinical-features/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"c59566b4-f12c-545c-8941-a7de38155871","slug":"clinical-features","fullItemName":"Clinical features","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 0b03bdd9-f413-4646-bd4f-a08e9698501a --><h2>When should I suspect blepharitis?</h2><!-- end field 0b03bdd9-f413-4646-bd4f-a08e9698501a -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item b4323288-b371-4f12-a9dd-451b6d3418d5 --><!-- begin field b59560ff-0700-437d-adcb-a15d9a55127d --><ul><li>Suspect blepharitis if the person has:<ul><li><strong>Characteristic symptoms (often intermittent, with exacerbations and remissions occurring over long periods):</strong><ul><li>Burning, itching and/or crusting of the eyelids.</li><li>Symptoms are worse in the mornings.</li><li>Both eyes are affected.</li><li>Recurrent hordeolum.</li><li>Contact lens intolerance.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Conditions associated with blepharitis:</strong><ul><li>Dry eye syndrome — for more information, see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/dry-eye-syndrome/\">Dry eye syndrome</a>.</li><li>Seborrhoeic dermatitis — for more information, see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/seborrhoeic-dermatitis/\">Seborrhoeic dermatitis</a>.</li><li>Acne rosacea — for more information, see the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/rosacea/\">Rosacea - acne</a>.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><ul><li>It is often not possible to differentiate between the different types of blepharitis clinically — typical features are summarized in Table 1.</li></ul><p><strong>Table 1.</strong> Features associated with the different types of blepharitis.</p><table><thead><tr><th scope=\"col\"> </th><th scope=\"col\">Staphylococcal blepharitis</th><th scope=\"col\">Seborrhoeic blepharitis</th><th scope=\"col\">Meibomian blepharitis</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"4\"><strong>Anterior eyelid</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Eyelash loss</td><td>Frequent</td><td>Rare</td><td>Unusual</td></tr><tr><td>Eyelash misdirection</td><td>Frequent in severe chronic cases</td><td>Rare</td><td>May occur with long-standing disease</td></tr><tr><td>Eyelid and eyelash deposits</td><td>Crusting with scales at base of lashes</td><td>Oily skin scales and greasy matted lashes</td><td>Foamy discharge on lid margin </td></tr><tr><td>Eyelid inflammation</td><td>Erythema (frequent), oedema and telangiectasia.</td><td>Erythema and oedema and telangiectasia — less marked than with staphylococcal blepharitis.</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Eyelid ulceration</td><td>Can occur in severe acute on chronic episodes.</td><td>—</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Eyelid scarring</td><td>May occur</td><td>—</td><td>Can occur with long-standing disease</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"4\"><strong>Posterior eyelid</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Meibomian glands </td><td>—</td><td>—</td><td>Dilated/visibly obstructed</td></tr><tr><td>Chalazion (tarsal or Meibomian cyst)</td><td>Rare</td><td>Rare</td><td>Sometimes multiple</td></tr><tr><td>Stye</td><td>May be recurrent</td><td>—</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"4\"><strong>Eye</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Conjunctivitis</td><td>Mild to moderate</td><td>Mild</td><td>Mild to moderate</td></tr><tr><td>Cornea</td><td>Corneal epithelial defects may occur<sup>†</sup></td><td>Corneal epithelial defects not usually present</td><td>Corneal epithelial defects may occur<sup>†</sup></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"4\"><strong>Skin</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Associated skin disease</td><td>Atopic eczema (rare)</td><td>Seborrhoeic dermatitis</td><td>Seborrhoeic dermatitis, acne rosacea</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"4\">† Detection requires slit-lamp examination and may require ophthalmology referral.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"4\"><strong>Data from:</strong> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">Lindsley, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">Putnam, 2016</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">American Academy of Ophthalmology, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">BMJ, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">College of Optometrists, 2018</a>]</td></tr></tbody></table><!-- end field b59560ff-0700-437d-adcb-a15d9a55127d --><!-- end item b4323288-b371-4f12-a9dd-451b6d3418d5 -->","topic":{"id":"210e4b01-890a-5a0a-a3cf-efcece1eb08e","topicId":"1bba37b4-ec1b-49d5-acc1-6fc1671711cf","topicName":"Blepharitis","slug":"blepharitis","lastRevised":"Last revised in April 2019","chapters":[{"id":"b93c0a0c-4692-53c9-843f-49ee05545451","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9c38019b-31fa-5b39-9bb8-b27769998a9b","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9620e929-162c-539c-b063-b0d2d792fc78","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"fd79cb69-88c9-53b3-a6a8-4bc9d0b0848f","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"ccbb8929-8463-57af-b3d5-cf785a546c74","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"4111c3c7-ee03-523b-800b-280e6b45dfbf","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"aff6bd9c-9a5d-5a90-9983-0fb81983feba","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"ec8eea31-e7ad-50f8-a443-eb9120f2bd11","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"7d5547f8-0c93-5d41-9cd4-d98e71ef7975","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"4e0b92f2-dd2a-568f-9ce8-bfcc52e4599d","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"960b987f-d9f7-5a39-8b20-715ba8988e6b","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"250fbd5e-7fdf-5849-bf02-a9c794a764ef","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE Quality standards"}]},{"id":"44811d5c-7af7-54f4-8fbe-e23a28523234","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"09fc8800-1ae4-546d-be0b-62e044edfca1","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"6899ed96-f696-5938-9656-d097419cff77","slug":"causes","fullItemName":"Causes"},{"id":"9a08c813-358a-52ed-8317-6734ad0caa2c","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"9261cec2-b5d4-5c5d-9e32-4a0d9acc38cb","slug":"prognosis","fullItemName":"Prognosis"},{"id":"48fb1bb9-46aa-5515-a112-656b86a86a56","slug":"complications","fullItemName":"Complications"}]},{"id":"3916f955-e558-5e75-911e-ae48f8579e84","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"c59566b4-f12c-545c-8941-a7de38155871","slug":"clinical-features","fullItemName":"Clinical features"},{"id":"23eadfb4-a45e-50b5-9d14-0f785ac86a84","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"a1f19a88-0a61-5514-b729-f6ba8636d70e","slug":"differential-diagnosis","fullItemName":"Differential diagnosis"}]},{"id":"aa038862-8424-552a-84d0-e962619a7e33","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"a41dab9c-d988-5d7a-813e-2d7a1658f5bc","slug":"management-of-blepharitis","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management of blepharitis"}]},{"id":"e0741730-0deb-5ab5-9f8a-0113b66dbe06","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"48e19546-bded-5436-9f23-e37a6fc78e36","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"b75f0439-fc4c-5236-954c-bfe59f6da9a5","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"b6a215d3-627d-577f-ba63-d0387c86ce0e","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"78dfcd62-db19-57fc-8f1f-0a100d3e4268","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"8e70896c-9149-59b5-b395-aa848fcd9ab2","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"4289ac7a-ea00-51b4-8b87-184e9a519291","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"28ab262f-aac6-5c78-badf-72aa21ca0119","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"3916f955-e558-5e75-911e-ae48f8579e84","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"793e3982-dcac-5f28-9e9b-4c34f850115a","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-d7a","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field a45553ec-20ce-431f-8929-2a85d49e4d74 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field a45553ec-20ce-431f-8929-2a85d49e4d74 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item d7a45617-aa64-4d8a-a9c8-9336c74f0331 --><!-- begin field d29c14af-c7d3-4910-9f68-7edbf3ab3f37 --><p>The information on the clinical features of blepharitis is based on clinical guidelines <em>Blepharitis – Preferred Practice Pattern 2018</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">American Academy of Ophthalmology, 2018</a>] and Blepharitis (lid margin disease) [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">College of Optometrists, 2018</a>], a Cochrane systematic review <em>Interventions for chronic blepharitis </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">Lindsley, 2012</a>] and expert opinion in review articles [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/blepharitis/references/\">Carlisle, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliogra